<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="entertain-v">entertain <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ˌentə'teɪn/    美 /ˌentər'teɪn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>招待；款待：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I don't entertain very often.
我不太经常请客。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It's easier to make a feast than to get the guests to come, and get the guests to come than entertain them properly.
办酒容易，请客难；请客容易，款客难。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>使欢乐；给...娱乐：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He <strong>entertained</strong> us <strong>with</strong> his stories and jokes. 
他讲故事、说笑话逗我们开心。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A museum should aim to entertain as well as educate. 
博物馆的目标应该娱乐与教育并重。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>entertainer /ˌentə'teɪnə(r)/ n [C]<br />
entertaining /ˌentə'teɪnɪŋ/ adj   </p></div>